  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> fennel seeds</strong> and cook for 2 min, then transfer them to small dish for serving&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Tip: watch them like a hawk to make sure they toast, not burn!</p>\r\n<p>Keep the pan, you'll use it later!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/579.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/579.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/579.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/579.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/579.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Trim the stalks off the&nbsp;<strong>aubergine<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and&nbsp;cut them<strong>&nbsp;</strong>in half lengthways</p>\r\n<p>Tear the aubergine halves into rough pieces using your hands (alternatively chop into large chunks)</p>\r\n<p>Tip: this is a rustic dish, so the aubergine doesn't have to be neat!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/579.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/579.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/579.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/579.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/579.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return&nbsp;your pan to a high heat with&nbsp;2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>vegetable oil</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the torn <strong>aubergine</strong> with a big pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cook for 3-4 min or until starting to brown</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, boil&nbsp;a kettle for your pasta</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/579.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/579.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/579.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/579.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/579.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>sausages</strong> open and squeeze the sausagemeat into the aubergine (this is a fun job for little hands!)</p>\r\n<p>Reduce the heat to medium-low and cook for a further 5-8 min or until both the sausagemeat and aubergine has browned &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/579.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/579.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/579.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/579.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/579.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>pasta</strong> to a pot of salted boiled water, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 8-12 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/579.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/579.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/579.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/579.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/579.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and slice the<strong> shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely</p>\r\n<p>Peel&nbsp;and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop&nbsp;the <strong>parsley</strong> stalks finely, keeping a small handful of leaves aside for garnish</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>shallot</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong> and <strong>parsley</strong> stalks to the sausage and cook for a further 3 min</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/579.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/579.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
